    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup today is anchored by **Kyle Tucker**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 81.43 against Paddack. The combination of an favorable opposing xERA of 4.64 and a favorable wind-out condition makes **Kyle Tucker** an elite start for both power and counting stats. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** also presents a strong profile (68.69) despite facing the lefty Suarez; his sustained high xwOBA and favorable lineup spot in the three-hole provide enough insulation to overcome the platoon disadvantage. Meanwhile, **Andy Pages** (66.19) is a standout value play today, benefiting significantly from a soft matchup against Paddack and advantageous wind conditions that boost his HR upside.\n\nOur most difficult decision of the day involved **Marcell Ozuna**, who fell just short of a starting berth with a score of 55.96. While his raw power remains a threat, the \"wind-in\" factor at his venue combined with the superior daily efficiency scores of our primary outfielders pushed **Marcell Ozuna** to the bench to preserve our limited game caps. Managers should also monitor the 40% rain risk hovering over the matchups for **Nolan Schanuel** and **Miguel Vargas**. Both players have been cleared to start with scores of 59.11 and 59.00 respectively, as their matchups against favorable pitching (Kay and Kochanowicz) outweigh the threat of a potential rain-shortened outing. We will be watching the radar closely, as any further deterioration in weather could necessitate a rapid pivot to our bench options.",
